nc:Activity.nc:ActivityDescriptionText: According to Ms. Wilson, her father and her are very close, talking and visiting each other regularly. She has not seen or heard from her father in three days and is concerned that something may have happened. She indicated that her father has no friends or relatives with which he might be visiting. She noticed that her father's car is missing from the garage, which was said to also be unusual since he does not take the car out in the rain and it has been raining for the last 5-7 days. She describes her father as a "home body with expensive tastes."
Caller believes father is missing. Has not seen or heard from him for 3 days. States this is very unusual and requests an officer drive by to check things out.

nc:Vehicle.nc:ItemDescriptionText: Has bumper sticker on trunk lid that reads, "Drive it like you stole it!"

ndexia:MissingPersonOccurrence.ndexia:ReportingOfficerNarrativeAccountD: I went to 1313 Mockingbird Lane, rang door bell, and no one answered the door. The door was locked. I checked the grounds. Nothing seemed out of order, though there was a weeks worth of mail and newspapers on the porch. I verified that there was no car present in the garage, which was also locked. I left my business card inside the front storm door and requested a phone call. This call is considered closed. Please enter Mr. Wilson in NCIC as a Missing Person upon completion of signed missing person report.

ansi-nist:PhysicalFeatureDescriptionDeta.ansi-nist:PhysicalFeatureDescriptionText: Bolts protruding from left and right side of neck
Tattoo of heart saying "mother I love you" on back
